      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> cornflour </strong>and<strong> </strong>2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>flour </strong>to a plate, season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and a generous grind of<strong> pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>flour mix</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>marinated</strong> <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to the <strong>flour mix</strong>, then press firmly into the mixture,<strong> </strong>making sure to evenly coat them on both sides – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p><p>Discard any remaining marinade</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1687256452210-x200.jpg",
